  "text": "The binding of p,p´-DDT to the TMD modifies the physicochemical environment of the transmembrane helices of the receptor. This in turn modifies the free energy landscape of the receptor, leading to p,p´-DDT acting as a positive allosteric modulator. In addition, the ectodomain of the receptor is proposed to behave as an inhibitor of the TMD [CITATION_1] . The binding of p,p´-DDT may also participate in the release of this inhibitory interaction, which may explain the enhanced response to hCG as well.",
